Are there good introductory texts and intermediate monographs
presenting categorical approaches to combinatorics and statistics?
I know of and admire *Une th=E9orie combinatoire des s=E9ries formelles* pa=
r
Andr=E9 Joyal,
cf. http://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Combinatorial_species,
but am seeking works which are in English,
and that actually develop the mainstream elementary theory
but using the categorical vernacular and results.

Presentation of topics significant in computer science
(cf. Knuth, Graham, Patashnik* Concrete Mathematics* for some examples of
such topics)
would also, of course, add interest.

